The most striking development was the visible repurposing of the Justice Department from neutral law enforcement into a political instrument. Attorney General Pam Bondi appeared before the Senate Judiciary Committee and refused to answer basic questions about dismantling anti\uc0\u8209 corruption units, closing investigations into allies, and handling the Epstein files. Senators pressed her on disbanding the FBI\'92s Foreign Influence Task Force, gutting the public integrity section, and dropping probes into Trump\'92s border czar Tom Homan despite a recorded $50,000 bribe offer. Her stonewalling was not just personal defiance. It signaled that the department\'92s leadership no longer feels bound to explain itself to Congress when the questions touch the president\'92s interests. That is a sharp break from past norms.\
