Around these marquee cases, the department\'92s structure was quietly altered to make such prosecutions easier and accountability harder. Bondi stripped the public integrity section of staff and authority, including its traditional role in approving charges against members of Congress. The bribery investigation into Tom Homan was closed after Trump took office, with Bondi insisting there was no credible evidence despite the recorded offer of contracts for cash. A whistleblower alleged that FBI agents were told to flag Epstein records mentioning Trump, while Bondi refused to say who gave that order or whether incriminating material existed. Democracy Forward sued the FBI and DOJ for ignoring a Freedom of Information Act request about the Homan recording. Taken together, these moves hollowed out the internal checks that once made it hard to use federal criminal law as a personal cudgel.\
