The reaction from the legal community underscored how far the department had drifted. A coalition of 282 former DOJ officials issued a public letter warning that the administration was destroying the department\'92s integrity by violating court orders, dismantling anti\uc0\u8209 corruption units, and targeting perceived enemies. They described a Justice Department that now shields allies, buries corruption probes, and reserves its harshest tools for those who cross the president. Their warning did not change policy in Week 38, but it did fix the pattern in the record. Future readers will see that insiders recognized the shift and said so while it was happening.\
