The White House did not accept that boundary. Messages leaked from a senior aide, Anthony Salisbury, showed him discussing plans with a Pentagon adviser to deploy the Army\'92s 82nd Airborne Division to Portland. Hegseth wanted Trump to sign a direct order, in part to spread the political risk. At the same time, a classified DOJ memo argued that the president could designate drug traffickers as enemy combatants and order lethal strikes on their boats under emergency economic powers. That memo was used to justify a strike on a vessel off Venezuela and, later in the week, a mistaken strike on a Colombian boat that likely killed Colombian citizens. The New York City Bar Association condemned these actions as illegal summary executions and urged Congress to remind the president of his limits. The administration\'92s answer was not to narrow its claims, but to talk openly about invoking the Insurrection Act to send troops into U.S. cities, with Stephen Miller asserting on television that the president had \'93plenary authority\'94 to do so.\
