Even as the courts wrestled with the Guard, federal agents on the ground escalated their tactics. In Broadview, outside Chicago, ICE agents used tear gas, pepper balls, and physical force against protesters, journalists, and even local officials. Viral videos showed agents firing into crowds and shoving credentialed reporters. The local police chief accused ICE of making false 911 calls that drained community resources. In Portland, federal officers pepper\uc0\u8209 sprayed a protester in a green inflatable frog costume by spraying into the costume\'92s air intake, then used tear gas on crowds hours after Judge Immergut\'92s ruling. In Chicago, agents shot Marimar Martinez after a vehicle chase; her lawyer said body\u8209 camera footage, still unreleased, showed an officer taunting her before firing. These were not isolated excesses. They were the visible edge of a security apparatus that now treated protests and immigrant neighborhoods as battlefields.\
