In the arc of Trump\'92s second term, Week 38 matters less for a single dramatic break than for the way it thickened the web of practices that make democratic recovery harder. Executive power continued to operate by acting first and forcing others to react, whether in deploying troops, striking foreign vessels, or reinterpreting worker protections. Law was used more openly as a weapon against political opponents, while anti\uc0\u8209 corruption tools were dismantled or turned inward. Federal power and the budget were wielded to punish disfavored states and cities. Information was managed through disinformation, access control, and intimidation of journalists and scholars. Yet courts, governors, former officials, and protesters did not simply yield. They blocked deployments, limited force, exposed abuses, and kept memory alive.\
